headlines.description: — Aston Villa enjoyed a third win in four Premier League games as it beat Bournemouth 3-0 at home with goals from Douglas Luiz, Jacob Ramsey and Emiliano Buendia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fans cheer Brooks' return in Bournemouth's 3-0 loss at Villa

headlines.description: Harvey Barnes netted a superb second-half equaliser to give Leicester City a 1-1 draw at Brentford in the Premier League on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes earns Leicester crucial point at Brentford

headlines.description: — The chances of Tottenham returning to the Champions League next season are starting to look a bit slimmer after the team threw away a two-goal lead at last-place Southampton on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Conte slams 'selfish' Tottenham after draw with Southampton

headlines.description: Leeds United moved out of the Premier League relegation zone after a thrilling 4-2 win at Wolverhampton Wanderers on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leeds beat Wolves 4-2 to boost survival hopes

headlines.description: — Chelsea's three-game winning streak in all competitions came to a halt as Everton came from behind twice to earn a 2-2 draw in the Premier League on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Everton halts Chelsea's run with 2-2 draw in EPL
